        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 6:26PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 626 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Heath Springs to 7 miles south of
Chesterfield. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lancaster, Cheraw, Kershaw, Chesterfield, Elgin, Heath Springs,
Westville, Cheraw State Park, Northeastern Technical College, Cheraw
Municipal Airport, Carolina Sandhills Wildlife Refuge, Mt Pisgah,
Irwin, Mcbee, Jefferson, Society Hill, Ruby, Patrick, Bethune, and
Chesterfield Ruby Middle School.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
